[Name] Allegro
[Summary] A portable game programming library.
[License] Freely Distributable
[Description] Allegro is a multi-platform game library for C/C++ developers that provides many functions for graphics, sounds, player input (keyboard, mouse, and joystick), and timers. It also provides fixed and floating point mathematical functions, 3D functions, file management functions, compressed datafile, and a GUI.
[Homepage] https://alleg.sourceforge.net/
